{{Infobox football match | title = 2006 Supercupa României | image = | event = 2006 [[Supercupa României]] | team1 = [[FC Steaua Bucureşti|Steaua Bucureşti]] | team1association = [[2005–06 Divizia A|Divizia A]] | team1score = 1 | team2 = [[FC Rapid Bucureşti|Rapid Bucureşti]] | team2association = [[2005–06 Cupa României|Cupa României]] | team2score = 0 | details = | date = 22 July 2006 | stadium = [[Stadionul Naţional (1953)|Stadionul Naţional]] | city = [[Bucharest]] | man_of_the_match1a = {{Flagicon|ROU}} [[Daniel Opriţa]] | man_of_the_match1atitle = | man_of_the_match1b = | man_of_the_match1btitle = | referee = [[Alexandru Tudor]] ([[Romanian Football Federation|Romania]]) | attendance = | weather = | previous = [[2005 Supercupa României|2005]] | next = [[2007 Supercupa României|2007]] }}
The '''2006 Supercupa României''' was the 9th edition of Romania's season opener cup competition. The match was played in Bucharest at [[Stadionul Naţional (1953)|Stadionul Naţional]] on 22 July 2006, and was contested between [[Divizia A 2005–06|Divizia A]] title holders, [[FC Steaua Bucureşti|Steaua]] and [[2006 Cupa României Final|Cupa României]] champions, [[FC Rapid Bucureşti|Rapid]]. Steaua won the trophy after a late goal by [[Daniel Opriţa]].
