{{Infobox football biography | name = Darwin Bonilla | fullname = Darwin Doronis Bonilla Salgado | image = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1990|8|6}} | birth_place = [[Chirilagua]], El Salvador | height = {{height|m=1.74|precision=0}} | currentclub = [[C.D. Águila|Águila]] | clubnumber = 24 | youthyears1 = 2002–2005 | youthyears2 = 2006–2007 | youthclubs1 = [[C.D. Dragón|Dragón]] | youthclubs2 = [[C.D. Águila|Águila]] | position = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Striker]] | years1 = 2008–2013 | clubs1 = [[C.D. Águila|Águila]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | nationalyears1 = 2011 | nationalteam1 = [[El Salvador national under-23 football team|El Salvador U23]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2013 | nationalteam2 = [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador]] | nationalcaps2 = 5 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | pcupdate = | ntupdate = }}
{{spanish name 2|Bonilla|Salgado}} '''Darwin Doronis Bonilla Salgado''' (born 6 August 1990 in [[Chirilagua]], [[El Salvador]]) is a former [[Salvadoran]] footballer who last played for [[C.D. Águila]] in the [[Primera División (El Salvador)|Salvadoran Premier League]].
==Club career== Bonilla's professional career began in July 2008 when he signed a contract with [[Salvadoran]] national league club, [[C.D. Águila]], after he had already joined them 2 years earlier from [[C.D. Dragón|Dragón]].<ref>[http://www.elgrafico.com/gol-nacional/primera/tabla-de-posiciones-apertura-2010/player/7/191.html Profile] - El Gráfico {{es icon}}</ref>
He made his professional debut on September 13, 2008, in a league match against [[C.D. Vista Hermosa]], and scored his first goal on November 5 that same year in a league match against [[C.D. Luis Ángel Firpo]].
On September 20, 2013, Bonilla was one of 14 Salvadoran players banned for life due to their involvement with match fixing.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-24184567 |title= El Salvador match-fixing: 14 footballers banned for life |publisher= BBC |accessdate=21 September 2013}}</ref>
