{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = VEN | NOCname = [[Venezuelan Olympic Committee]] | games = Winter Olympics | year = 2014 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.covoficial.com.ve }}&nbsp;{{es icon}} | location = [[Sochi]] | competitors = '''1''' | sports = 1 | flagbearer = [[Antonio Jose Pardo Andretta]]<ref name=sochi2014ocfb>{{cite web |url=http://www.olympic.org/Documents/Games_Sochi_2014/Flagbearers_Sochi_2014_Opening_Ceremony.pdf |title=Sochi 2014 Opening Ceremony - Flagbearers |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=7 February 2014 |website=olympic.org |publisher=[[Sochi 2014 Olympic and Paralympic Organizing Committee]] |accessdate=7 February 2014}}</ref> ([[2014 Winter Olympics Parade of Nations|opening]] and [[2014 Winter Olympics closing ceremony flag bearers|closing]])<ref>{{cite web|title=Sochi 2014 Closing Ceremony - Flagbearers|url=http://www.olympic.org/Documents/Games_Sochi_2014/Flagbearers_Sochi_2014_Closing_Ceremony.pdf|publisher=The [[International Olympic Committee]] (IOC)|date=February 23, 2014|accessdate=23 February 2014}}</ref> | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Venezuela]]''' competed at the [[2014 Winter Olympics]] in [[Sochi]], [[Russia]] from 7 to 23 February 2014. The team consisted of one athlete in [[alpine skiing]].<ref name="a">{{cite news |last= |first= |date=22 January 2014 |title=Venezolano Antonio Pardo estará en Sochi |url=http://www.correodelorinoco.gob.ve/otros-deportes/venezolano-antonio-pardo-estara-sochi/|language=Spanish|trans-title=Venezuelan Antonio Pardo will be in Sochi |newspaper=[[Correo del Orinoco]] |location= |publisher= |accessdate=24 January 2014 }}</ref> This marks the country's return to the [[Winter Olympics]] after missing the [[2010 Winter Olympics|previous games]] four years ago.
==Competitors== {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center; font-size: 95%" |- ! width=200|Sport !! width=60|Men !! width=60|Women !! width=60|Total |- | align=left|[[Alpine skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics|Alpine skiing]] | 1||0 ||1 |- ! Total ||1|| 0 ||1 |}
== Alpine skiing == {{main|Alpine skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics}} According to the quota allocation released on January 20, 2014 Venezuela had qualified one athlete.<ref name="quota">{{cite web |url=http://data.fis-ski.com/media/olympic-games/quota-20-01-2014-6.pdf |title=Summary of Quota allocation as per 20.1.2014 |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date=20 January 2014 |website=www.fis-ski.com |publisher=[[International Ski Federation|FIS]] |accessdate=20 January 2014}}</ref> Pardo is the fifth ever [[Venezuela]]n to ever qualify for the [[Winter Olympics]] and the first ever to qualify in a snow sport.<ref name="a"/> Pardo entered the [[2014 Winter Olympics opening ceremony|opening ceremony]] showing of his dance moves, which set off a [[social media]] buzz.<ref>{{cite news |last=Rush|first=Curtis |date=7 February 2014 |title=Antonio Pardo, Venezuelan skier, captures hearts at Sochi Olympics opening ceremonies|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/sochi2014/2014/02/07/antonio_pardo_venezuelan_skier_captures_hearts_at_sochi_olympics_opening_ceremonies.html |newspaper=[[Toronto Star]]|location= |publisher= |accessdate=14 February 2014 }}</ref>
Pardo was the final starter in a field of 109 athletes in the [[Alpine skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics – Men's giant slalom|giant slalom]] and quickly crashed after starting the race, thus receiving an official status of did not finish the race. Pardo summarized the race as, "it was not my fault,... one of the skis just fell off. If it was my fault, well...nothing I can do. But something that really doesn't belong to me is kind of upsetting".<ref>{{cite news |last=Baldwin |first=Alan |editor1-first=Martyn |editor1-last=Herman |date=19 February 2014 |title=Olympics-Alpine skiing-Venezuelan banker unfazed by crash |url=http://in.reuters.com/article/2014/02/19/olympics-alpineskiing-venezuela-idINL3N0LO2TZ20140219 |newspaper=''[[Reuters]]'' |location=[[Rosa Khutor]], [[Russia]]|publisher= |accessdate=19 February 2014 }}</ref>
